INFORMATION ‼️
‘Cag Kebab’ is yet another delicious kebab variety of Turkish cuisine. It is originated from the Erzurum city which locates at the heart of the Eastern Anatolia Region of Turkey. At first sight, Cag Kebab may look like a Döner Kebab to you; however, it is different in how it made and taste.

‘Cag Kebab’ is made with the combination of boneless lamb ribs and boneless leg of lamb meat. On the other hand, Döner Kebab is made with a combination of boneless veal meat, lamb meat, and tail fat. When it comes to cooking styles, Cag Kebab cooks at the wood fire on a horizontal rotisserie; however, Döner Kebab cooks at a specially designed electric vertical rotisserie.

Slicin’ the 6 lb RibEye into Thick-cut Steaks. Smokin’ the family of RibEyes to 115 IT indirect with Natural Lump and Hickory Chunks.Searin’ the 2 lb RibEyes to 125 IT direct on the grill Large over Flammin’ Natural Lump🔥 Toppin’ with Fresh Parsley Chimichurri.Pairin’ the RibEyes with Grilled Veggie Kabobs and a Red-White-Blue Spinach Salad. RibEyes rubbed with Gaucho Steakhouse, Pink Himalayan Salt, Black Peppercorns, and binded with Olive Oil.... Veggie Kabobs seasoned with Garlic Herb and Pink Salt!💨🔥🥩

Miguel of @cooking_with_fire___ fires up some cheesy chimichurri quesadillas on the @nomadgrills. Marinate with chimichurri sauce (Miguel's recipe below) then sear for 4 minutes per side. Let rest for 5 minutes before slicing. Add cheese to your tortilla and top with heaps of meat. Garnish with cilantro, red onion, lemon juice, creamy chipotle sauce and enjoy.

= Chimichurri =
• 1 bunch flat leaf parsley
• 2 tsp oregano
• 4 minced garlic cloves
• 1 tsp chili flakes
• 1/4 cup red wine vinegar
• 1/2 cup olive oil

• Salt & pepper to taste

= Creamy Chipotle Sauce =
• 3 tbsp sour cream
• 1 tbsp chipotle
• 1 tsp cilantro
• Juice of 1/2 a lemon
• Salt & pepper to taste

The king of outdoor cooking, Max of @grillhunters, takes on the king of seafood on his @nomadgrills — melted with some garlic, herbs and lemon compound butter. Max's tribe is stoked for the smell of some smoked lobster in the air! 🦞🦞 #nomadgrills

= INGREDIENTS =
• 2 Live Lobster

= COMPOUND BUTTER =
• ½ cup butter softened
• 2 tbsp lemon juice
• 2 cloves garlic minced
• 1½ tbsp fresh chives chopped
• 1½ tbsp fresh rosemary chopped
• 1½ tbsp lemon zest
• ½ tsp kosher salt
• ½ tsp pepper

= INSTRUCTIONS =
• Fire up coals in a chimney.
• While the coals are heating up, mix all the compound butter in a small bowl.
• In the center of a plastic wrap, put the compound butter and wrap tightly both ends.
• Place in the refrigerator while prepping the lobster.
• Slice both lobsters lengthwise, inserting the knife between both eyes first to neutralize nervous system.
• Place your hot coals under the cooking grates.
• Melt about 2 tbsp of the compound butter and pour on the raw lobster meat.
• Place the half lobsters, meat down, on the smoking grates.
• After 5 minutes, turn the lobsters over, place a cube of compound butter on top and cook for another 3 minutes.

INFORMATION ‼️
‘Cag Kebab’ is yet another delicious kebab variety of Turkish cuisine. It is originated from the Erzurum city which locates at the heart of the Eastern Anatolia Region of Turkey. At first sight, Cag Kebab may look like a Döner Kebab to you; however, it is different in how it made and taste.

‘Cag Kebab’ is made with the combination of boneless lamb ribs and boneless leg of lamb meat. On the other hand, Döner Kebab is made with a combination of boneless veal meat, lamb meat, and tail fat. When it comes to cooking styles, Cag Kebab cooks at the wood fire on a horizontal rotisserie; however, Döner Kebab cooks at a specially designed electric vertical rotisserie.

INGREDIENTS 👨‍🍳:

Here is the recipe (8 people):
Dry brine 2 kg of rib eye. The next day rub 2 tablespoons of mustard, sprinkle on all sides with 3 tablespoons of finely chopped rosemary and another 6 tablespoons of the beef rub:

Beef Rub:
3 tbsp coarsely ground black pepper
1 tbsp granulated white sugar
1 tbsp onion powder
2 teaspoons mustard powder
2 teaspoons of garlic powder
2 teaspoons of chipotle or cayenne powder
mix it up - and you still have something in reserve for the next time.

The roast goes on a spit and cooks at approx. 170 ° C for 1 1/2 hours.  8 (sweet) potatoes are placed in the charcoal basket as a side dish. 

For the compound butter

1/2 pound butter (room temp.)
1/2 bunch of finely chopped parsley
1/2 bunch of finely chopped chives
1 teaspoon beef rub
1 teaspoon salt
1 teaspoon apple cider vinegar
2 cloves of garlic (to taste)

Mix and chill.

Slice the roast into 8 equal slices, serve with the grilled potato and herb butter.

📽: @laurent.dagenais BISON TOMAHAWK Recipe 🥩🦬

Za’atar and Maple Roasted Carrots 🥕

Herbs & Lemon Yogurt 🌱🍋

INGREDIENTS 👨‍🍳

For Bison

•Bison Tomahawk
•2-3 Rosemary Sprigs
•3-4 Garlic Cloves
•2 Tbsp Butter
•1 Tbsp Olive Oil
•Salt & Pepper

For Carrots

•12-15 Carrots
•2-3 Garlic Scapes
•3 Rosemary Sprigs
•2 Tbsp Olive Oil
•2 Tbsp Maple Syrup
•2 Tsp Za’atar Spices
•Salt & Pepper

For Herbs & Lemon Yogurt

•4 Tbsp Greek Yogurt
•2 Tsp Za’atar Spices
•1 Lemon (Zest & Juice)
•Chives
•Flat Parsley
•1 Tbsp Olive Oil
•Salt & Pepper

Preparation

1.Place your carrots and garlic scapes on a roasting pan, drizzle with olive oil, maple syrup and season with Za’atar spices and salt & pepper. Roast on medium high heat for 45 minutes, toss around every 10 minutes.

2. Season tomahawk heavily with salt and pepper. In a hot cast iron pan, sear bison on all sides until a beautiful golden crust is formed. Discard cooking oils and add butter, rosemary and garlic. Baste bison with butter for 2-3 minutes. Set tomahawk aside to rest on a grill for 7-8 minutes before cutting into 1 inch slices.

3. In a mixing bowl, add all the ingredients from the yogurt section above and drizzle on your carrots before eating.

Enjoy 🙏❤️

Sesame Teriyaki Burnt Ends 🥩

Love Steak? Follow us: @steakvideos
📽By: @maxthemeatguy

Burnt ends are arguably the best bite in BBQ. 

Cube beef, season, and smoke at 250F for 3-4 hours. Wrap with your favorite beer and continue cooking until tender (~4 more hours). Prepare sauce, coat burnt ends, finish in oven for 15 minutes. Top with green onion and sesame seeds.

Sauce:
1 cup soy sauce
8T mirin
6T brown sugar
8t sesame oil
4 chopped garlic cloves
2t grated ginger 
4t sesame
Reduce by ~half

🎶 Sheesh - @iambemax
